&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Analyst,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To: Director, Client Success, US&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: New York, NY (Hybrid)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the newly integrated Place Exchange by Broadsign SSP, Broadsign’s Client Success Organization is growing and looking for a talented Account Analyst to light up the world. Broadsign is a growing software company with a mission to make buying, selling, and delivering out-of-home media easier than ever. We power the screens that inform and entertain the world, and we’re looking for passionate people to help us scale the next generation of digital-out-of-home (DOOH) advertising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Analyst, you will be a vital engine behind our growth. Joining our Media Planning team, you will act as a bridge between Sales, Client Success, and our diverse roster of clients. This is a fast-paced, detail-oriented role designed for someone eager to become an expert in the emerging programmatic OOH channel. You aren&#39;t just supporting campaigns; you are mastering the business model and ensuring our clients receive exceptional service at every touchpoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Media Planning &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sales Directors and Client Success Managers by generating high-impact media plans and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full lifecycle of an opportunity, from media planning to execution and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate and communicate deal requirements for won opportunities, ensuring total accuracy for every campaign launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Relationship Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong internal relationships with Sales, Client Success, and Ad Ops to ensure a seamless customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key liaison with publisher sales contacts to advance client campaigns and troubleshoot needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing and Operations to transform campaign successes into compelling client collateral.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domain Expertise &amp;amp; Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a fluent expert in the digital OOH landscape and its role within omnichannel marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of our inventory integrations across both domestic and international markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the &quot;go-to&quot; resource for the team, executing tasks accurately and proactively meeting all deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to team documentation and process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you need to perform in this job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience Level:&lt;/strong&gt; 0-2 years of experience in the programmatic media landscape, specifically within an SSP, DSP, or Ad Operations environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interpersonal Prowess:&lt;/strong&gt; Outstanding communication skills and a natural ability to thrive in a team-oriented environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Aptitude:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong analytical base; experience with business intelligence or reporting tools is a significant plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; An upbeat, energetic, and self-motivated approach to work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; The ability to stay organized and excel in a fast-paced, evolving industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive, Programmatic Sales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To: &lt;/strong&gt;Regional VP, Programmatic Sales &amp;amp; Client Success&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;New York, NY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the newly integrated Place Exchange by Broadsign SSP, Broadsigns Sales Organization is growing and looking for a talented Senior Account Executive to light up the world. Broadsign is a leading programmatic ad tech company on a mission to make buying, selling, and delivering out-of-home media easier than ever. Our platform powers the world’s most successful OOH and retail media businesses while enabling agencies and brands to seamlessly plan and execute dynamic OOH campaigns across the globe. Come light up the world as an &lt;strong&gt;Account Executive, Programmatic Sales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your day-to-day will vary but your mission is simple; as a key member of our Programmatic Team, you will be taking full responsibility for business development activities of enterprise accounts by educating buyers on the new opportunities brought forth by our products. Your territory will consist of media buyers from agencies and brands. You’ll put your sales experience to use by determining client needs and recommending optimal programmatic DOOH proposals and supporting agency-wide agreements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;*This is a remote role based in either New York!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Of course, if this role speaks to you, you’re someone who has;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-5 years enterprise-level sales experience in the media world; you understand agencies and what advertisers care about&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven understanding of the digital programmatic ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in engaging with new buyers by introducing them to the benefits of programmatic DOOH and the innovative advertising opportunities via the Broadsign programmatic stack&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation skills - you know how to craft a pitch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great communication and collaborative approach with teammates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical proficiency in programmatic advertising, including a solid understanding of audience targeting, measurement metrics, and DSP workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational excellence with CRM tools like Salesforce and a proactive, self-starter mentality toward solving problems and identifying new opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and the ability to prioritize tasks effectively in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we bring to the table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt; Health Care coverage packages available!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wellness &amp;amp; Fitness: &lt;/strong&gt;$500 annual Wellness fund (in local currency) for health, fitness, specialist fees, and office set-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paid Time Off: &lt;/strong&gt;Minimum 3 weeks vacation, 5 floater days, 5 sick/personal days, 2 volunteer days, and 3 paid training days.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retirement Savings:&lt;/strong&gt; 401k matching (100% match on the first 2% of eligible earnings, and 50% match on deferrals between 2% and 6%).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Office Perks:&lt;/strong&gt; Meal allowance for employees working from centralized offices (Tuesday-Thursday)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Giving Back:&lt;/strong&gt; Charitable Donation Matching for causes aligned with Broadsign’s Core Values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Family Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Parental leave salary supplement to support you during important life transitions.

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Operations Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To:&lt;/strong&gt; Director of Ad Operations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Montreal, QC / Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the newly integrated Place Exchange SSP, Broadsign’s Sales Organization is growing and looking for a talented Campaign Ops Associate. Broadsign is a leading programmatic ad tech company on a mission to make buying, selling, and delivering out-of-home media easier than ever. Our platform powers the world’s most successful OOH and retail media businesses while enabling agencies and brands to seamlessly plan and execute dynamic OOH campaigns across the globe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the programmatic ecosystem expands, maintaining optimal system performance and deep technical harmony between platforms is paramount. The Campaign Ops Associate sits at the core of our technical operations, serving as the technical lead within a cross-functional pod. In this role, you will bridge the gap between technical complexity and business logic, taking ownership of the integrity and yield performance of the Place Exchange and Broadsign supply-side ecosystem. You will run deep diagnostics, untangle complex delivery anomalies, and build automation workflows that keep our exchange operating at peak health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Participate in daily AdOps meetings to align on pod strategy, review live actions, and sync via automated Slack channels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive Monitoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and monitor custom dashboards using Looker or other analytical tools to track campaign health from pre-launch to execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issue Diagnosis:&lt;/strong&gt; Investigate abstract delivery issues to determine if faults are internal or stem from the programmatic ecosystem, executing direct resolutions or escalating as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Code Inspection:&lt;/strong&gt; Review underlying parameter values and system configurations within the code to anticipate system needs and coordinate with Engineering, Product, and Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Projects:&lt;/strong&gt; Own at least one dedicated technical project based on your passions and pending Broadsign platform needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you need to perform in this job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 2-4 years of professional experience in Ad Tech, with a strong preference for individuals who have worked within an SSP or DSP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Fluency:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong ability to interpret complex system signals and bid-stream data; high proficiency in relational database querying and utilizing SQL or Looker logic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Solving:&lt;/strong&gt; A true &quot;builder&quot; mindset with a deep interest in utilizing AI, machine learning, or automated prompt engineering to continuously improve operational workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; A highly collaborative teammate who thrives in cross-functional pod environments, possesses a strong ownership mentality, and excels at bridging communication gaps between engineering, product, external demand partners, and clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we bring to the table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt; Complete company insurance plan (health, dental, vision, travel) effective from day one, 100% employer-paid.&lt;/li&gt;
