&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Stack Software Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To: Director of Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Amsterdam, Netherlands (Hybrid / Remote)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Broadsign is a growing software company with a mission to make buying, selling, and delivering out-of-home media easier than ever. Our software is operated by some of the most successful out-of-home businesses and powers impactful, compelling campaigns seen across the world.&lt;br&gt;Come join us as a &lt;strong&gt;full-stack software Developer&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;Amsterdam&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Full-Stack Software Developer, you will play a pivotal role in driving the evolution of our industry-leading out-of-home media platforms by bridging the gap between robust backend architectures and sleek, responsive user interfaces. This role is designed for a developer who thrives on clean code, innovation, values strong engineering practices, and wants to see their work impact millions of viewers globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join our Amsterdam-based &lt;strong&gt;OutMoove&lt;/strong&gt; team at Broadsign to build and optimize end-to-end features for our programmatic digital out-of-home Demand-Side Platform (DSP).&lt;/p&gt;
